values:
Beware: This is really long

You don't realize it as its happening.  Everything seems the same day in and day out.  Then one day you stop and look around to realize..."I'm not a kid anymore."  It's a scary realization.  You don't think you've changed all that much but when you look back on your life it all seems so far away now.  The way your mind worked seems so juvenile now.  And now it's time to start looking ahead into the future.  Thinking about jobs and careers.  I want to think "I'm only a Junior...I shouldn't have to worry about this until next year."  The problem is that if I wait until next year who knows what will happen.

So, now I'm in this new major and have to start thinking in a different direction.  For these past two years I was almost certain I wanted to teach.  The more I've thought about it, the more I realize that I don't want to spend my life STUCK in a classroom.  And I should have known that this wasn't for me the moment I thought if my future career as "stuck."  I know I like kids.  I love to teach.  The general music classroom is not for me.  I lost sight of MusEd being my fall back.  Performance was my passion.  I may not be the best at it, but I love it.

I should have been a theater major from the start and I knew it.  Instead, I decided that Music Ed. was the smart choice.  It would guarantee me a job out of college.  But what good is a guaranteed job, if I'm not going to enjoy what I've spent my college years learning how to do.  

Changing my major was a good move for me.  It might seem pointless to spend 4 years at a music conservatory and not get my Bachelor's of Music degree, but I'm not stressed.  I'm enjoying all of my classes.  This semester is for me.  I'm taking classes I enjoy and doing my best to become the person I've always wanted to be.  I'm finally organized, I'm getting my work done and focusing now on how I'm going to become the best I can be.

My next step is to change my voice teacher.  This one is harder than it seems.  My teacher and I got along rather well from the beginning.  I was very open-minded to learning about classical music since I had never studied it.  I let her teach me everything she could.  But it seems now, 2 years in, I've hit a wall.  I've never dealt with that before.  I stopped working with previous teachers in my life for various reasons outside of my control but this one I need to end myself.  

It's really hard when you've spent 2 years building up a relationship with this person.  You see them once a week and they are practically your mentor.  The problem is that the direction I want to go in vocally is something she knows very little about.  I want to sing theater rep. and her knowledge is highly limited to music pre-1950.  Not to mention she is trying to make my voice thicker than it is and it's beginning to wear on me.  My vocal stamina doesn't exist anymore.  I'm disconnected in my lessons now because no matter what I say she doesn't get it.  The worst part is that she's blind to it all.  I've spoken to her about my rep. issues and she just doesn't see a problem.  It's frustrating me beyond belief.

Anyway, I really like her.  It's not like I haven't learned anything because I have.  I've learned a lot but I have 3 semesters left to get my voice into shape for Grad-school auditions.  I really want to my masters in Musical Theater and I will not be accepted with the limited training I've had thus far. So, I'm meeting her next week to discuss all of this in great detail.  I'm just really nervous because I don't want to upset her but I need this for me.

Sorry I've rambled for so long.  Kudos to you if you made it through this whole thing.  Now, I'm off to bed for a good night's rest.
It's been a wonderful night... :D  I'd love to explain but it's a long story.  Either way, life is great right now.

I leave my house: 8 1/2 hours
I check in at the college: 9 1/2 hours

I can't wait.  Even though I know it's not good bye and that I'll still see all of you at some point I'm gonna miss having all of you around 24/7.  It's something I've always counted as a constant.  I want to leave for college, and have the new experiences and meet new people but at the same time I want my friends there with me experienceing these new things right next to me.  I know that that's not possible, so now I have a reason to update more often than I usally do.  I need to keep everyone posted on life at college.   And all of you need to do the same.  It'll be like I have a window into your lives and you one into mine.  It'll be like we never parted.  I'm gonna go before I get to deep for my own good.  Goodnight everyone.

So, today was Meg's party.  I had a blast.  The party ran from 1:00-midnight.  I was there from 12:45-11:00.  At about 12:30 Meg calls me to come help her set up since her parents left and be a buffer.  So I went and very quicly found the dip and salsa and we set up trays. Then I hung out and talked to people and had a generally good time.  Meg then sent me to get her gas, pick up the Badminton net and drop Concetta off in Heritage Valley. Since Heritage Valley stretches throughout all of twp. practically we got lost.  But we found our way eventually. When I got back John was there along with a few other people.

The fun started when we had to unravel the Badminton net from Danielle's house. That thing was a mess.  It took 4 of us and 20 minutes to untangle this thing.  Me, Carl, John, and Joe Teichman.  After much tugging pulling yelling and frustration the net lost. Steve arrived a bit later with coffee gelato for Mooch.(lol) Then he spent a good 3 hours doing nothing but playing Badminton.  He's a beast.  The trouble didn't start until Trevor got there.  We hung out for awhile, then he came up behind me and put his hands on my shoulders menacingly.  Amanda turned to me and asked why I looked so scared.  Those of you who were at Meg's sweet 16 know exactly where this story's going.  Except this time he accomplished the task.  He threw me over his shoulders, emptied my pockets and started for the deck stairs.  Just like last time he put me down, but as I started to run he grabbed me again.  Before I knew it I was up in the air and then back down in the pool.  Still in all my clothes.  I came out soaked. My shoes are still wet.  No sooner was I out and he picked me back up and repeated.  

So, I figured I'd strip down to my bathing suit and put my clothes in the dryer for awhile.  As soon as I started drying myself off I was back in the pool...again...damn trevor.  I had a great time.  Any of you who were there know it was great those of you who weren't missed out.  Now, it's bedtime.  Night all.

So, I haven't updated in, oh, FOREVER!!!!!!!!!! I usually don't have much to say. As far as college goes I applied to 3 different schools. I applied to TCNJ, UArts, and Westminster. Westminster was my top choice but I wasn't sure if I'd get in b/c competition is kinda high there. So My first letter to come back was TCNJ...Rejection. My Second letter was UArts...Accepted with the "Promising artist scholarship" which was about $3,000 something or so. Lastly was Westminster (Those bums made me wait forever), Accepted with the Dean's scholarship of $9,000 a year b/c of my GPA and SAT scores. Needless to say I'm going to Westminster Choir College next year to major in Music Education. It should be fun. Life around here has been pretty boring lately. There's not much going on. Don't get me wrong, it's relaxing and I like the Drama free-ness, but as far as things to do, there's not much. I'm getting tired of the same old routine. I feel like I'm stuck. Graduation is coming up and I can't wait for that, but I have the feeling that things still won't change and this summer is just going to be hectic. Oh well, it'll be a change of pace anyway. Hopefully I'll have a job. I've applied to Blockbuster, The Learning Express and WoW Video. I'm also going to apply to Commerce Bank b/c Ann just told me that they're hiring for this summer too. I'm hoping to do a show this summer as well but quite frankly I don't know if I really want to. We'll see. Oh, and I stole this from Andrea b/c it seemed interesting:

So yeah, updating compulsively like everyone else really isn't my thing.  I'm kinda feeling like crap right now and I don't really know why.  It's just one of those days I suppose.  I still have a lot of shopping left to do and absolutely no time to do it.  I accidentally spent $80 on christmas gifts last friday and I only bought 3 gifts.  Go me!  My dad gave me $120 to go shopping with, so i should have $40 left right?  Wrong.  I then ended up spending 20 of it on applebee's with Allison and Katie Saturday night after our lovely trip to Maple Shade.

They were having a Candle-light vigil for a soldier from Maple Shade who died in Iraq.  I felt really bad because I didn't know him, but I helped out to the best of my ability anyway.  I had actually planned just to hang at Allison's house that night but I got a "wake-up" call from Maryann that morning asking me to come and help.  Considering I enjoy helping out over there I gladly accepted.  Luckily Allison likes helping as much as I do b/c I realized she was going to be my only way there when my mom told me I couldn't take the car.  When we finished singing there, Maryann decided to invite herself to mass which kinda took me aback, but it was cold and I was tired and cranky and didn't feel like spending the next few minutes explaing to her why she couldn't come while choosing my words as carefully as possible so as to not offend her.  I feel bad but I need to let her know that she doesn't belong there.  She's under the impression that she can come to church with us every week and we don't want her there.  But I won't get into that now.  That's a conversation for later.

As far as me feeling like crap, it's one of those days.  One of the days where you feel so distant from the people you were once so close to.  I usually don't talk about it b/c I don't want to burden people with my thoughts.  I feel bad.  But I just wish things were different.  I wish I felt as close to these people as I did, not even a year ago.  Senior year was supposed to be sooo great.  And it's relatively decent, but it's not at all what I had hoped for.  It feels like everything is changing soo fast.  I know it's supposed to change but didn't think it would start to until close to the end of the school year.  I really want things to go back to how they were, but I know that can't happen.  Granted I feel closer to people I wasn't close to before but so much more distant from the ones I want to be close to.    

I want soo bad just to go back to a time when things were better.  Don't get me wrong, it's not like they're horrible.  It's just not a place I want to be in.  For the most part I don't talk to people about it b/c they all have their own problems that they're dealing with and to listen to someone else bitch and complain a lot is the last thing they need to hear.  Instead, I put on a smile and try to be there for those who need it.  I guess you can say I have a complex.  Sometimes I wish I didn't things would be soo much easier if I didn't always think I had to be the strong one.  It's just that it always seems like everyone else isn't all that stable.  I can't help myself sometimes.  Ususally, I can handle my own problems, so I don't post.  But today I felt like posting and had not a clue what I was going to say.  And hear I go rambling.  Oh well.  Things will get better if I just give them time.  They say "time heals all wounds" and for the most part it's true.  So, I'll leave it up to time to fix whatever feels like it's gone horribly wrong. Until then I'll attempt to handle my own issues.  I'm sure there are more but that's the only thing on my mind right now.

I don't usually update, so I figured "Why Not?!"  It's thanksgiving.  So, this year my my crazy Hispanic Grandparents decided to go with my Aunt and her Southern, Jewish husband down to Alabama for this wonderful holiday they call "Sangsgibbing" in true broken english.  I feel bad for my uncles family.  They have to deal with my picture happy grandmother who, from what I was told, decided not to waste time. She started taking pictures of the house as soon as they arrived.  She was acting like a tourist outside of the home of her son-in-law's parents.  God bless those people.  

Back home however, my dad decided that we would host this lovely holiday for the rest of the family.  It was quite calm for once.  My grandmother usually causes all of the trouble on holidays.  Those of you who don't know what holidays with foriegn relatives are like, you're lucky.  However this was a good year.  No hispanic food this sangsgibbing.  My mom and nan cooked.  Good ol' fashioned Turkey(not pork), homemade mashed potatos, corn and a lovley pumpkin pie.  It was delicious.  Then on Christmas eve it'll be back to the good old Pork, Black peans and rice with Flan for dessert.

Speaking of Christmas it's one month away and I have to start my shopping with the money I'll be getting from the job I was currently offered at Target!  Unfortunatley I don't know what to get anyone, so please feel free to let me know what you'd like for the holiday, that's within my limited budget.  That's all for now.  Maybe I'll update again in a month or so.  Happy Thanksgiving to all!
